This paper proposes a Transferable Ranking Convolutional Neural Network (TRk-CNN) for image classification of glaucoma, glaucoma suspect, and normal eyes. The paper focuses on the application of deep learning in medical image classification, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The proposed TRk-CNN model is designed to effectively handle the inter-class relationship between the three classes, which is a common challenge in multi-class classification problems. This makes it relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) community, which focuses on developing intelligent systems that can reason about complex relationships. The paper also evaluates the proposed model on a glaucoma image dataset, which is a common application area for medical image analysis (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach for combining the weights of the primitive classification model, which is relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) community.
